This application reads the data for a conference as defined in http://www.conference-publishing.com/ConfEventData-JSON.php. All the data contained in the JSON is stored in `data` and in `records`.

xzRrUa6lvJb8El7DycWOp1nc.text: Use `is cached` to test if you already have the data stored locally. In conference, it is usually the case that participants don't have internet access so caching is very important.

xQNm1OjEXPzaks7klxHy1SSQ.text: For this demo, we download the data from the CHI 2012 conference hosted on Microsoft Research servers. The parser expects valid JSON back.
